    "recap_headline": "California State University Northridge Athletics",
    "recap_text": "NORTHRIDGE, Calif.\n---CSUN Baseball rallied from nine runs down only to fall short by one run in a 17-16 loss to UC San Diego on Friday at Robert J. Hiegert Field.\nColton Boardman\nfinished 4-for-5 with four runs scored while\nMatthew Pena\nhad three hits including two home runs and three RBI and\nVaughn Coleman\ndrove in four runs and blasted a homer in a 15-hit Matador attack.\nCSUN scored 15 of its 16 runs over the last four innings, but UC San Diego scored two in the ninth and held on for the win.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nIn a game that featured a combined 32 runs, 30 hits and seven errors, the Tritons jumped ahead with three runs over the first three innings for a 3-1 lead. UCSD would pull away in the middle innings, scoring a single tally in the fourth on a solo homer from Nick Costello and another in the fifth on an RBI single from Alex Leopard. In the sixth, the Tritons batted around in a five-run inning with the big blow coming off the bat of J.C. Allen who hit a three-run homer.\nTrailing 10-1 in the sixth, the Matadors fought back when\nMatthew Thomas\nhit a leadoff double and Pena followed with a two-run homer. CSUN later loaded the bases with one out for\nWill Linberg\nwho drew a walk to force in another run. A Triton error off the bat of\nAndrew Becker\nallowed two more runs to come across, making it a 10-6 game through six innings.\nMichael\u00a0Crossland gave the Tritons a bit of breathing room with a two-run homer in the top of the seventh. UCSD would threaten further, loading the bases with two outs, but Matador reliever\nLogan Miller\nstruck out Cal Elvis to end the threat.\nCSUN again was far from done down 12-5. Pena led off the seventh inning with a solo homer while a Boardman double and\nTrent Abel\nsingle produced another run.\nJehee Lee\ndrew a walk to bring Coleman to the plate. The freshman would deliver a timely three-run homer to make it a 12-11 game.\nNot to be deterred, the Tritons answered with three runs in the top of the eighth as Gabe Camacho and Allen had RBI hits. With the lead at 15-11, the Matadors forged yet another rally in their home half of the eighth. CSUN loaded the bases with one to start before Coleman drove in a run on an infield hit. Moments later, Linberg knocked in two runs with an RBI single and Becker squared the game at 15-15 with an RBI hit of his own.\nCSUN loaded the bases once more with two outs in the eighth but could not come away with the go-ahead run. Seeing their big lead slip away, the Tritons went to work at the plate in the ninth, scoring twice more on a Camacho two-run homer.\nThe Matadors threatened one last time in the bottom of the ninth, scoring a run with two outs after Coleman reached on an error in left field, scoring Boardman from third base. Linberg stepped to the plate next, but was retired on strikes by Julian Cazares, ending the marathon four-hour and 35 minute game.\nNOTES OF THE GAME\nCSUN drops to 10-7 overall and 2-2 in Big West play while UC San Diego improves to 5-10 overall and 1-0 in conference.\nLinberg drove in three runs on just one hit while he also walked twice.\nPena's multi-homer game was his third of the season. He has now homered eight times this season.\nColeman's home run in the seventh was his first of the season.\nSeven CSUN pitchers saw action in the contest.\nTraig Oughton\nbegan the game, tossing three innings and allowing four runs.\nMiller, who retired one batter, was the only pitcher between the two teams to not allow a run.\nUP NEXT\nCSUN plays game two of its weekend series with UC San Diego on Saturday at 2 p.m. on ESPN+.\n#GoMatadors"
  },
